‐	<small>[symbol]</small><br>short dash, used in hyphenated words, and in breaking syllables where no accent is used. But sometimes the typists used the normal hyphen, or the long dash for that purpose. The normal hyphen is the same length as the long dash, but one pixel higher in the character box.<br>In headwords, in the full ASCII version, this short dash is represented by the asterisk "*".<br>短破折号，用于连字符单词，以及在不使用重音时划分音节。但打字员有时使用普通连字符或长破折号来达到此目的。普通连字符与长破折号长度相同，但在字符框中的位置高一个像素。<br>在词目中，在全ASCII版本中，此短破折号由星号"*"表示。
–	<small>[symbol]</small><br>long dash, one pixel removed from left will fuse with left long dash<br>长破折号，从左侧移除一个像素可与左长破折号融合
–—	<small>[symbol]</small><br>combination for a very long dash. In the original typing, the dash char 208 was used for both non-breaking hyphen (in hyphenated words), and for the em-dash used as an introductory mark for various segments. The em-dash should be distinguished from the hyphen, but that conversion hasn't yet been done. In the full ASCII version, a double hypen "--" represent the m-dash.<br>组合成极长破折号。在原始输入中，字符208既用于非断字连字符（在连字符单词中），也用于作为各种部分引导标记的em破折号。em破折号应与连字符区分开，但此转换尚未完成。在全ASCII版本中，双连字符“--”表示em破折号。
—	<small>[symbol]</small><br>--<br><mdash/<br><graphic horizontal line>Represents the long dash, used for the em dash which often precedes certain sections within a definition, and which separates some sections, such as wordforms or collocations within a collocation segment. This is replaced in the full ASCII version by a double hyphen, "--".<br>长（全角）破折号<br>表示长破折号，用作em破折号，通常用于定义内某些部分之前，或用于分隔某些部分（如词形或搭配段内的搭配）。在全ASCII版本中被双连字符“--”替代。
―	<small>[symbol]</small><br>graphic horizontal line<br>图形水平线
